@modernize
We are migrating a Java test automation project written in IntelliJ IDEA
to .NET 8 using C#.

The existing project uses Cucumber (BDD), but we want to completely remove
BDD concepts (feature files, step definitions, Given/When/Then).

Please:
- Propose a modern .NET 8 test automation architecture
- Use xUnit (preferred) or NUnit
- Convert Cucumber-based tests into clean, code-first test classes
- Avoid BDD terminology
- Follow SOLID and clean test design principles
- Assume long-term maintainability is a priority
- Keep page object model


Additional Notes; All tests should use the same login method with normal user,
Except these two feature's tests ; contractConfirmationByDirector.feature and contractConfirmationByManager.feature
tests created from contractConfirmationByDirector.feature will use "RETAIL_DIRECTOR"
tests created from contractConfirmationByManager.feature will use "RETAIL_MANAGEER" 
passwords are in env/staging.users.yml
